Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc. opens position in GIMO / Gigamon Inc. - Fintel.io

































Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc. opens position in GIMO / Gigamon Inc.









SecurityGIMO / Gigamon Inc.
InstitutionHussman Strategic Advisors, Inc.

                        Shares50,000
Value
                        $ 1,778,000


May 01, 2017
            - Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc. has filed a 13F-HR form disclosing ownership of 50,000
            shares of Gigamon Inc. (NYSE:GIMO)
            .
        
Other investors with positions similar to Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc. include
                First Manhattan Co , Nordea Investment Management Ab, Alliancebernstein L.p. , New York State Common Retirement Fund, Jacobs Levy Equity Management, Inc,  and Swiss National Bank.
            
Gigamon Inc. has declared a standard industrial code (sic) of 7374 which
        is the "Computer Processing and Data Preparation and Processing Services" industry.
        
            Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc.'s top industries are
             
                 "Heavy Construction Other Than Building Construction Contractors" (sic 16), 
                 "Rubber And Miscellaneous Plastics Products" (sic 30),  and 
                 "Real Estate" (sic 65).
        
        

HUSSMAN STRATEGIC ADVISORS(More Info)
This Page
GIMO / Gigamon Inc.(More Info)









Hussman Strategic Advisors, Inc. ownership holdings in Gigamon Inc. (NYSE:GIMO) are shown in the following table.




                    Don't Miss an Event
Create an Alert



13F Filings
The Security, Class, and CUSIP columns in the table below are shown exactly as filed by the investor.
        We do our best to track continuity of investments through acquisitions, and this will be reflected in
        the table as changes in names and cusips.
In addition to descriptive data, performance of the investment
        is shown over time. To calculate quarterly performance, we first calculate cost basis of the shares purchased during the quarter, then use
            that to calculate gross profit. Quarterly return is Gross Profit / Starting Portfolio value.
Note that cost basis is calculated and stored in thousands, so small quarterly changes in shares frequently
            result in a cost basis of zero.




